author: entaik.bsky.social
content: After the Paris Olympics 2024 boxing gender row, I have learnt this. The presence of a Y chromosome does not mean one is male, but it is a good indicator. The "make-male hormone" gene, known as SRY determines one's sex. If one with an XY chromosome has lost the SRY gene, one develops female anatomy.
